# ============================================================================
# DOCUMENTATION FILES - ALWAYS COMMIT (DO NOT IGNORE)
# ============================================================================
# The following files SHOULD be tracked in git:
# - LICENSE (CVSL 1.0 license file)
# - README.md, [internal], ROADMAP.md, FAQ.md, AI-CONTEXT.md
# - docs/*.md (all documentation)
# - docs/archive/*.md (archived legacy documentation)
# These are explicitly NOT ignored below.

# ============================================================================
# Operating System Files
# ============================================================================
.DS_Store
.DS_Store?
._*
.Spotlight-V100
.Trashes
ehthumbs.db
Thumbs.db
*~

# iCloud Drive conflict duplicates (macOS creates "file 2.ext" copies)
* 2.*
* 3.*

# IDEs and Editors
# Ignore .vscode/ contents (not the directory itself) so the carve-outs below
# can re-include specific files. Per gitignore(5): a re-include rule cannot
# resurrect files under a parent directory that is itself excluded.
.vscode/*
# Team-shared VS Code config carve-outs (per docs/policies/mcp-server-policy.md §3).
# Personal settings (.vscode/settings.json, launch.json, etc.) remain ignored.
!.vscode/mcp.json
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea/
[internal]*
